{{UK-film-bio-stub}}

Rice Bowl Cover measuring 1 3/4" high and 7 1/2" in diameter. This is a lid to a large rice bowl decorated with a medallion of the double happiness and long-life symbol in the center. The border of it shows two peonies with their foliage in blue underglaze. The ground appears with a grayish-green tonality. The cover is glazed on the inside as well and is used as an eating container. Yi (Joseon) Dynasty Bowl 19th century.
From the private collection of Paul V. and Elizabeth J. Colaianni.
Photograph by Elizabeth J. Colaianni, and appears here with her permission. Evidence of Permission can be found under contents #8 at the following link: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk:Korean_Pottery:_Categorized_by_Periods
