{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2011}} {{Infobox NCAA team season | Mode = football | Year = 1961 | Team = The Citadel Bulldogs | Image = Citadel Athletics Script.jpg | ImageSize = 150 | Conference = Southern Conference | Division= | ShortConference = SoCon | TSNRank = | FCSCoachRank = | Record = 7‚Äì3 | ConfRecord = 5‚Äì1 | HeadCoach = [[Eddie Teague]] | HCYear = 5th | OffCoach = | DefCoach = | OScheme = | DScheme = | StadiumArena = [[Johnson Hagood Stadium]] | Champion = SoCon champion | BowlTourney = | BowlTourneyResult = }} {{1961 Southern Conference football standings}} The '''1961 The Citadel Bulldogs football team''' represented [[The Citadel, The Military College of South Carolina]] in the [[1961 NCAA football season]]. The Bulldogs were led by fifth year head coach [[Eddie Teague]] and played their home games at [[Johnson Hagood Stadium]]. They played as members of the [[Southern Conference]], as they have since 1936. In 1961, The Citadel won its first Southern Conference championship.
After the season, the Bulldogs declined two bowl invitations. The first to be offered was the [[1961 Tangerine Bowl|Tangerine Bowl]]. The Citadel had appeared in the previous edition of this small-college bowl in [[1960 Tangerine Bowl (December)|1960]] and elected to decline the repeat trip. Later, the Bulldogs declined an invitation to the [[Aviation Bowl]].
