'''Hilden S√ºd station''' is in the city of [[Hilden]] in the German state of [[North Rhine-Westphalia]]. It is on the [[D√ºsseldorf‚ÄìSolingen railway]], which was opened on 3 January 1894 by the [[Prussian state railways]].<ref name=L2671>{{cite web| url= http://nrwbahnarchiv.bplaced.net/strecken/2671.htm| title= Line 2671: Hilden - Solingen Hbf|work=NRW Rail Archive |publisher= Andr√© Joost |accessdate=24 October 2011 |language=German}}</ref> The station was also opened in 1976 or 1977<ref name=operations/> and it is classified by [[Deutsche Bahn]] as a [[German railway station categories|category 5 station]].<ref name= categories/>

The station is served by [[S1 (Rhine-Ruhr S-Bahn)|line S 1]] of the [[Rhine-Ruhr S-Bahn]], running between [[Dortmund Hauptbahnhof|Dortmund]] and [[Solingen Hauptbahnhof|Solingen]] every 20 minutes during the day.<ref name=station>{{cite web| url= http://nrwbahnarchiv.bplaced.net/bf/8002828.htm| title= Hilden S√ºd station |work=NRW Rail Archive |publisher= Andr√© Joost |accessdate=24 October 2011 |language=German}}</ref>

