{{Use Indian English|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox person | name = Chakradhara Satapathy | image = File:Chakradhara Satapathy Statue.JPG | alt = | caption = A statue of Chakradhara satapathy at [[kalabuda]] Market | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[kalabuda]], [[odisha]], [[India]] | death_date = 2006 | death_place = [[kalinga Hospital]], [[Bhubaneswar]] | nationality = [[India]]n | other_names = | known_for = | occupation = [[Politician]] }}
'''Chakradhara Satapathy''' was the former [[Member of the Legislative Assembly (India)|MLA]] of the Patakura assembly constituency. He was elected from the Patakura assembly constituency to the state assembly as a [[Praja Socialist Party]]<ref>{{cite web |title=MLA Chakradhar Satpathy Profile {{!}} PATKURA Constituency |url=http://naveenpatnaik.com/MLA-Chakradhar-Satpathy-of-PATKURA-constituency-922.html |website=naveenpatnaik.com}}</ref> (PSP) candidate in 1967 after defeating former chief minister [[Biju Patnaik]]. Mr.Satapathy, who began his career as a schoolteacher, resigned from his job in 1964 to join the PSP. In 1965, he was elected as the chairman of the Garadapur block.He was the resident of [[Kalabuda]] Village<ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/news-feed/nm11/former-orissa-mla-c-satapathy-dies/article1-103010.aspx Former Orissa MLA C Satapathy dies] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331101105/http://www.hindustantimes.com/news-feed/nm11/former-orissa-mla-c-satapathy-dies/article1-103010.aspx |date=31 March 2014 }}</ref>
He joined the Congress in 1971.
Satapathy was also involved in social work in his constituency Patakura.
In May 2006 he was staying in his village named as [[Kalabuda]] in the coastal district of [[Kendrapada district|Kendrapada]], when he was 76, was admitted in the Kalinga Hospital and died.<ref>[http://www.nerve.in/news:2535002903 Veteran Orissa leader dies at 76 ]</ref>
Satapathy is survived by three daughters and a son.
