'''Mikhail Lobukhin''' ({{lang-ru|–ú–∏—Ö–∞–∏–ª –õ–æ–±—É—Ö–∏–Ω}}) is a Russian [[principal dancer]] of the [[Bolshoi Ballet]].
==Biography== Lobukhin was born in [[Saint Petersburg]], [[Russia]]. In 2002 he graduated from [[Vaganova Ballet Academy]] with a bachelor's degree in arts and the same year joined [[Marinsky Theatre]]. Eight years later he joined [[Bolshoi Ballet]] where he played many [[solo (dance)|solo]] roles but also appeared as a ''young man'' at the ''[[Leningrad Symphony]]'', ''prince'' in [[Cinderella (Prokofiev)|Cinderella]], ''Daphnis'' in ''[[Daphnis and Chloe]]'', and ''[[Ivan the Fool]]'' at the [[The Little Humpbacked Horse (ballet)|Little Humpbacked Horse]] among others. In 2010 her appeared as ''Basilio'' in the [[Don Quixote (ballet)|Don Quixote]] which was performed at the [[Novosibirsk State Academic Opera and Ballet Theatre]] and next year played a role of a ''Bahram Shah'' in [[Seven Beauties (ballet)|Seven Beauties]] at the [[Azerbaijan State Academic Opera and Ballet Theatre]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.bolshoi.ru/en/persons/ballet/630/|title=Mikhail Lobukhin|publisher=Bolshoi Ballet |accessdate=October 10, 2013}}</ref>
