{{Infobox lake | name = Shelton Lake | image = | caption = | pushpin_map = Vancouver Island | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Vancouver Island]], [[British Columbia]] | coords = {{coord|49|07|00|N|124|19|00|W|region:CA-BC_type:waterbody_source:dewiki|display=inline,title}} | lake_type = Natural lake | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = Canada | length = | width = | area = | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | islands = | cities = }}
'''Shelton Lake''' is a lake located on [[Vancouver Island]] at the head of South [[Englishman River]] north west of [[Nanaimo Lakes]].<ref>http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/16251.html</ref>
==Fishing==
Wild populations of native [[coastal cutthroat trout]] are found in Shelton Lake.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.env.gov.bc.ca/wsd/water_rights/wap/vi/englishman_river/plan.pdf |title=Microsoft Word- plan.doc |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=2011-10-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140520165250/http://www.env.gov.bc.ca/wsd/water_rights/wap/vi/englishman_river/plan.pdf |archivedate=2014-05-20 |df= }}</ref>
